---
// WhatJustHappened.astro
// What the demo shows — bullet summary + signal example
---

<section class="section reveal" id="what-happened">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="what-happened">
      <h2 class="what-happened__title">What the demo shows</h2>
      <ul class="what-happened__list">
        <li>the agents agree a contract before sharing context</li>
        <li>the relay enforces a fixed output schema</li>
        <li>invalid free-text output is rejected</li>
        <li>both sides receive the same bounded signal</li>
        <li>a signed receipt records what governed the session</li>
      </ul>

      <pre class="what-happened__signal font-mono"><code>{JSON.stringify({
  compatibility_signal: "PARTIAL_ALIGNMENT",
  friction_band: "HIGH",
  aligned_dimensions: ["company_commitment", "growth_ambition"],
  divergent_dimensions: ["revenue_strategy", "product_direction"],
  escalation_required: true,
}, null, 2)}</code></pre>

      <p class="what-happened__coda">
        The point is not to trust the model to be discreet.<br>
        The point is to constrain what can leave the session.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .what-happened {
    max-width: var(--content-max);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .what-happened__title {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .what-happened__list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .what-happened__list li {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-text);
    padding-left: 1.2em;
    position: relative;
  }

  .what-happened__list li::before {
    content: '\2014';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
  }

  .what-happened__signal {
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--color-bg-elevated);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .what-happened__coda {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
